{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04426/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04426"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:44:26"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man and woman get into their car."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04426","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04426"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/canvas/1/ac25f365-7ca9-4c81-88d7-148ad31b898a","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T13:46:24.616Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In this scene, Alma will offer to take the wheel of Reynolds’s car. On a broader, symbolic level, she is taking control of the relationship. This scene is followed by another from Alma’s fireside chat with Dr. Hardy in which she describes Reynolds’s depressive “episodes.” She is coming to understand her lover much more clearly.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:698.3171080319077,468.98327465272985,199.66499999999985,64.88590909090908"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/canvas/1/6a55139d-14df-4255-9cab-9731d530b17d","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T13:47:11.469Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In an interview, PTA speaks to the symbolism of this scene: “‘In my experience, and the experiences that I’ve seen of the people around me, there is a never-ending shift of power in a relationship: Who’s driving? And who’s criticizing the driver? . . . That’s kind of a natural thing that we all deal with if we decide to share this life with somebody. In the movie, we just crank it all up to 10 as a way to highlight and underline it’” (Ugwu, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW38641646 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/26/movies/daniel-day-lewis-and-paul-thomas-anderson-on-how-they-created-phantom-thread.html?action=click&amp;module=RelatedCoverage&amp;pgtype=Article&amp;region=Footer\"><u>Daniel Day-Lewis and Paul Thomas Anderson</u></a>”).</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04426/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:23.061899784533253,29.40201347820178,143.01563287947562,125.33408976298546"}}}]}]}]}